{"id":1285243705,"question_id":13,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"1 year, 1 month","timestamp":1718132995,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"10 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1285243705/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"12.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int romanToInt(string s) {\n        // Define a map to store the Roman numeral symbols and their corresponding values\n        unordered_map<char, int> romanValues = {\n            {'I', 1}, {'V', 5}, {'X', 10}, {'L', 50},\n            {'C', 100}, {'D', 500}, {'M', 1000}\n        };\n        \n        int total = 0;\n        int n = s.length();\n        \n        // Iterate through each character in the string\n        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {\n            // If the current value is less than the next value, subtract it\n            if (i < n - 1 && romanValues[s[i]] < romanValues[s[i + 1]]) {\n                total -= romanValues[s[i]];\n            } else {\n                // Otherwise, add the current value\n                total += romanValues[s[i]];\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return total;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":60}
